, 
<figureCitation box="[257,330,1339,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–38" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1858,1881]" captionTargetBox="[252,1325,207,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1344,193,1841]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 35–38. SEM images of cerci and distiphalli of Peckia spp. 35–36. Peckia (Peckia) hillifera (Aldrich), specimen from Pará, Bragança (MPEG) 35. Cercus in left lateral view; arrow points to pointed projection. Scale bar = 150 µm. 36. Peckia (Peckia) uncinata (Hall), specimen from Pará, Serra Norte (MPEG); cerci in dorsal view; arrow points to spines. Scale bar = 100 µm. 37–38. Peckia (Peckia) chrysostoma (Wiedemann), specimen from Pará, Belém (MPEG). 37. Distiphallus in lateral view; arrow points to juxtal lateral plate. Scale bar = 100 µm. 38. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus in left lateral view. Scale bar = 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456130/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">37–38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[341,413,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–74" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1853,1876]" captionTargetBox="[185,1433,200,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[150,1436,193,1832]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 69–74. Peckia (Peckia) chrysostoma (Wiedemman), female from Pará, Belém (MPEG). 69. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 70. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 71. Spermatheca in lateral view. 72. Abdomen in posterior view. 73. Abdomen in dorsal view. 74. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 67 = 4 mm; 68–69 = 0.5 mm; 70–72 = 2 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456143/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">69–74</figureCitation>
