<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1410,2011]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,548,1410,1435]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Description of female terminalia.</emphasis>
Posterior margin of T5 elliptical, brown, with golden microtrichosity dorsally and gray microtrichosity laterally (
<figureCitation box="[550,684,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–74" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1853,1876]" captionTargetBox="[185,1433,200,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[150,1436,193,1832]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 69–74. Peckia (Peckia) chrysostoma (Wiedemman), female from Pará, Belém (MPEG). 69. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 70. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 71. Spermatheca in lateral view. 72. Abdomen in posterior view. 73. Abdomen in dorsal view. 74. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 67 = 4 mm; 68–69 = 0.5 mm; 70–72 = 2 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456143/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 72–74</figureCitation>
). T6 divided into two halves, brown, with golden microtrichosity and a row of setae near posterior margin. Spiracles 6 and 7 located on T6. T8 absent (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1198,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–74" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1853,1876]" captionTargetBox="[185,1433,200,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[150,1436,193,1832]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 69–74. Peckia (Peckia) chrysostoma (Wiedemman), female from Pará, Belém (MPEG). 69. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 70. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 71. Spermatheca in lateral view. 72. Abdomen in posterior view. 73. Abdomen in dorsal view. 74. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 67 = 4 mm; 68–69 = 0.5 mm; 70–72 = 2 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456143/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Epiproct triangular, covered with long setae. Cercus covered with long and fine setae. Hypoproct covered with long and fine setae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 69–74" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1853,1876]" captionTargetBox="[185,1433,200,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[150,1436,193,1832]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 69–74. Peckia (Peckia) chrysostoma (Wiedemman), female from Pará, Belém (MPEG). 69. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 70. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 71. Spermatheca in lateral view. 72. Abdomen in posterior view. 73. Abdomen in dorsal view. 74. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 67 = 4 mm; 68–69 = 0.5 mm; 70–72 = 2 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456143/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). ST6 square, covered with robust setae near posterior margin. ST7 rectangular, with setae restricted to posterolateral margin. ST8 wider than long, with short setulae and a pair of robust lateral setae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[251,341,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–74" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1853,1876]" captionTargetBox="[185,1433,200,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[150,1436,193,1832]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 69–74. Peckia (Peckia) chrysostoma (Wiedemman), female from Pará, Belém (MPEG). 69. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 70. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 71. Spermatheca in lateral view. 72. Abdomen in posterior view. 73. Abdomen in dorsal view. 74. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 67 = 4 mm; 68–69 = 0.5 mm; 70–72 = 2 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456143/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Spermathecae globular, with parallel grooves restricted to distal half and a small rounded chamber where they receive the spermathecal duct (
<figureCitation box="[732,816,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–74" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1853,1876]" captionTargetBox="[185,1433,200,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[150,1436,193,1832]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 69–74. Peckia (Peckia) chrysostoma (Wiedemman), female from Pará, Belém (MPEG). 69. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 70. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 71. Spermatheca in lateral view. 72. Abdomen in posterior view. 73. Abdomen in dorsal view. 74. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 67 = 4 mm; 68–69 = 0.5 mm; 70–72 = 2 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456143/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
